ðŸ”¹ Step 2: Setup the Scan Target

If scanning your own PC, use:

localhost

or your systemâ€™s IP address (check with ipconfig on Windows / ifconfig or ip addr on Linux).




---

ðŸ”¹ Step 3: Run the Scan

In Nessus, create a new scan â†’ select Basic Network Scan.

Enter target (127.0.0.1 or your IP).

Start the scan.

The scan may take 30â€“50 mins depending on your system.



---

ðŸ”¹ Step 4: Review Results

After scanning, Nessus/OpenVAS will generate a report.

It lists vulnerabilities with severity levels:

Critical (Red)

High (Orange)

Medium (Yellow)

Low (Green/Blue)




---

ðŸ”¹ Step 5: Research Fixes

For each issue:

Read the description.

Search fixes (e.g., update OS, patch software, disable weak services, firewall rules).



---

ðŸ”¹ Step 6: Document Findings

Make a simple report file (Word/Notepad/Markdown). Include:

1. Tool used (Nessus/OpenVAS)


2. Target (localhost / IP)


3. Top vulnerabilities found (name + severity)


4. Suggested fixes


5. Screenshots of scan results


